   Filing a Complaint -- What Happens Now?

   When you want to file a complaint, your first need to make an effort to
   resolve your dispute with the company. . .before you contact us.

   If your utility service is in threat of disconnection, please call the
   Consumer Affairs section directly at 1-800-562-6150

   Visit our
   Consumer Page
   [0.6CE!OpenElement&FieldElemFormat=gif]
   More Helpful Info in our newsletter
   Free wallet card can save you $$$ when using a pay phone

   You can file a complaint using our on-line complaint form.
       Please provide as much information as you can, including what
       company is involved, the nature of the dispute, and what steps
       you've taken to resolve it yourself. Once we've completed our
       investigation, our staff will contact you to discuss the results.
       We may also contact you during the investigation with questions.
       You may file a complaint by any one of the following methods:

     * Calling the Consumer Affairs section toll free at 1-800-562-6150.
     * Requesting a hard-copy complaint form to fill out and mail in.
     * Filing electronically directly from this website using our
       electronic form.

   The UTC regulates only privately or investor-owned companies. If your
   dispute is with a Public Utility District or municipal utility, you
   will need to contact that utility.

   If your issue involves an interstate telecommunications service, you
   can file an online complaint with the Federal Communications
   Commission.
